### Why the long transition?

With no population growth and modest (\delta), the Solow model with (Y=A\sqrt{K}) converges **very** slowly—depreciation only gradually “makes room” for net investment to raise (K). Doubling (A) jumps (Y) on impact, but (K) inches up year by year.

